H0.text: Which US city began as a trading post on the Chisholm Trail in the 1860’s and is now the largest city in Kansas. Kansas City

H1.text: Which US city began as a trading post on the Chisholm Trail in the 1860’s and is now the largest city in Kansas. Topeka

H2.text: Which US city began as a trading post on the Chisholm Trail in the 1860’s and is now the largest city in Kansas. Lawrence

H3.text: Which US city began as a trading post on the Chisholm Trail in the 1860’s and is now the largest city in Kansas. Wichita

A4.text: Wichita began as a trading post on the Chisholm Trail in the 1860s

A5.text: Wichita is the largest city in Kansas and the 49th largest city in the United States, according to the 2020 census
